{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Longer custodial sentences & cost orders for Vehicle Taking Without Consent",
        "additional_details": "I believe the current sentencing council guidance does not lead to rehabilitation to the offenders, as some will just reoffend. I speak for others outside of the county, as I think this is a country-wide problem. I am also asking the government to consider mandating greater use of cost orders, to help ensure that the guilty party pay the full amount of any damages that they cause to the victims.",
        "background": "The maximum penalty for Vehicle Taking Without Consent is a 26-week custodial sentence. I am asking the government to reclassify the offence to allow for longer MANDATORY sentences: 52 weeks for Category 1 offences, 28 for Category 2, and 14 for Category 3.",
